title: Japan zoo culls 57 monkeys carrying 'invasive' genes | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Japanese zoo culls 57 snow monkeys after finding they carried 'invasive' genes Takagoyama Nature Zoo in the city of Futtsu in Chiba prefecture east of Tokyo, housed 164 simians which it believed were all pure Japanese macaques Officials discovered one-third were crossbred with the rhesus macaque Japanese law bans possession of invasive species, and allows them to be culled 57 native snow monkeys were killed by lethal injection Published: 10:08 GMT, 21 February 2017 | Updated: 03:25 GMT, 22 February 2017 32 shares
